--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Modifications made by Devotica Labs (Apache-2.0 §4(b) "stated changes")
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  * Hardened input DEFAULTS to a fintech-safe posture (see the `# Devotica
    fintech default` annotations in variables.tf):
      - endpoint_private_access      false -> true
      - endpoint_public_access       true  -> false   (private-only API by default)
      - oidc_provider_enabled        false -> true     (IRSA on by default)
      - enabled_cluster_log_types    []    -> all five control-plane log types
      - cluster_log_retention_period 0     -> 365 days
      - deletion_protection_enabled  false -> true
      - kubernetes_version           1.21  -> 1.31      (current supported minor)
      - encryption-config KMS key deletion window 10 -> 30 days
  * Added a `check "public_endpoint_restricted"` guardrail (main.tf) that
    flags an open public endpoint left at 0.0.0.0/0.
  * Replaced the upstream Cloud Posse CI/CD, issue templates, Atmos config,
    and Go (terratest) suite with the Devotica governance shape: the central
    reusable CI from devotica-labs/terraform-shared-config, conftest policies
    from devotica-labs/terraform-policies, release-please + cosign keyless
    signing + CycloneDX SBOMs, terraform-docs auto-update, Dependabot
    auto-merge, a Python architecture-diagram renderer, and native
    `terraform test` unit/contract/integration suites.
  * Rewrote README.md, examples/, and added SECURITY.md, CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md,
    CONTRIBUTING.md, CHANGELOG.md, NOTICE.

